like a packet of salts
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:go through (usu. somebody, occ. something) like a packet (Br. dose) of salts, to go through (somebody, something) very quickly (eg. spend money extravaganty; run, penetrate, pass through opposition players etc)
Origin:[none]
